main event: A civilian observed a peculiar object in Bradenton, Florida on June 17, 1963.
interesting points: The observation lasted for seven seconds and was described as resembling a meteor or satellite,It was noted that the object traveled along the horizon,The sighting resulted in a conclusion that it could be possible satellite debris or a meteorite,There were no photographs captured at the time of the sighting,The report was part of the Project Blue Book study conducted by the United States Air Force.
sighted object: an object similar to a meteor or satellite
